{
  "texts": [
    "The approach allowed for the identification of top-ranking molecules that exhibited sufficient structural and scaffold novelty, synthesizability, and a desired bioactivity profile across multiple targets.",
    "While molecular novelty has been extensively discussed in recent literature, most studies mainly focus on descriptor similarity using structural fingerprints 65, 66.",
    "We showed that incorporating additional scaffold criteria can enhance the novelty of top-ranking molecules.",
    "By assigning higher weights to different descriptors, distinct outcomes were observed.",
    "When higher weights were assigned to the ECFP fingerprint descriptor, the generated molecules exhibited higher structural similarity to known ligands."
  ]
}